<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?><feed xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom' xmlns:apps='http://schemas.google.com/apps/2006'>
    <title>Mail Filters</title>
    <author>
        <name>Dan Rue</name>
        <email>dan.rue@linaro.org</email>
    </author>

    <!--

        Gmail filters are powerful but difficult to manage in the UI. For example,
        in the UI, there is no easy way to specify filter order. Also, there is no
        way to stop filtering - all emails will hit all filter rules, which means
        that order is important.

        Maintaining filters in XML and then importing them solves the order
        issue. The multiple-match issue can be solved with complex rules that
        match and then have lists of exclusions. Alternatively, and rules to
        positively match emails I want to see, star them, and then exclude
        starred emails from subsequent rules.

        The easiest way to develop new rules is to write them in the UI, save
        them, and then export them. Advanced search operators can be found @
        https://support.google.com/mail/answer/7190

        Inbox Zero - I prefer to keep any email I intend to ever read in my
        inbox, and clear them out quickly (daily at worst), so the filters are
        actually quite minimal. Mostly they just allow me to get small subsets
        of mailing lists to my inbox using positive matches in Phase 1.

        Structure:

            Phase 1: Identify emails that should stay in inbox and star them.
                Examples: Mailing list posts addressed to me
                          Mailing list posts from certain individuals or with certain subject
            Phase 2: Identify emails I never want to see and archive them (unless they're starred).
                Examples: Auto-generated emails that have no value to me
            Phase 3: Identify emails I want to label and remove from inbox (unless they're starred).
                Examples: High volume mailing lists

    -->


    <!-- Phase 1: Star things I always want to see  -->
    <!-- To me specifically, but not from bots (so, probably from a human) -->
    <entry>
        <category term='filter'></category>
        <title>Star Personal Mail</title>
        <!-- Don't star these senders -->
        <apps:property name='from' value='-builds@travis-ci.org -projects@linaro.org -bugzilla-daemon@bugs.linaro.org -it-services@linaro.org'/>
        <apps:property name='to' value='dan.rue@linaro.org'/>
        <apps:property name='shouldStar' value='true'/>
    </entry>

    <!-- Stable review threads started by Greg -->
    <!-- Only the first message contains "stable review" in subject -->
    <!-- The patches themselves have a patch-specific subject instead. -->
    <entry>
        <category term='filter'></category>
        <title>Star stable review threads</title>
        <apps:property name='subject' value='PATCH stable review'/>
        <apps:property name='hasTheWord' value='list:&lt;stable.vger.kernel.org&gt;'/>
        <apps:property name='shouldStar' value='true'/>
    </entry>


    <!-- Phase 2: Stuff I never need to see -->
    <!-- Archive straight away -->
    <entry>
        <category term='filter'></category>
        <title>Build bot for Mark Brown</title>
        <apps:property name='from' value='Build bot for Mark Brown broonie@kernel.org'/>
        <apps:property name='hasTheWord' value='list:linaro-kernel.lists.linaro.org'/>
        <apps:property name='shouldArchive' value='true'/>
        <apps:property name='hasTheWord' value='-label:starred'/> <!-- Exclude starred -->
    </entry>
    <entry>
        <category term='filter'></category>
        <title>Olaf&apos;s autobuilder</title>
        <apps:property name='from' value='Olof&apos;s autobuilder &lt;build@lixom.net&gt;'/>
        <apps:property name='shouldArchive' value='true'/>
        <apps:property name='hasTheWord' value='-label:starred'/> <!-- Exclude starred -->
    </entry>


    <!-- Phase 3: Apply labels and remove from inbox -->
    <entry>
        <category term='filter'></category>
        <title>stable list - skip inbox, unless starred</title>
        <apps:property name='to' value='stable@vger.kernel.org'/>
        <apps:property name='hasTheWord' value='list:&lt;stable.vger.kernel.org&gt;'/>
        <apps:property name='label' value='lists'/>
        <apps:property name='shouldArchive' value='true'/>
        <apps:property name='hasTheWord' value='-label:starred'/> <!-- Exclude starred -->
    </entry>

    <entry>
        <category term='filter'></category>
        <title>LTP - skip inbox, unless starred</title>
        <apps:property name='to' value='ltp@lists.linux.it'/>
        <apps:property name='label' value='lists'/>
        <apps:property name='shouldArchive' value='true'/>
        <apps:property name='hasTheWord' value='-label:starred'/> <!-- Exclude starred -->
    </entry>

